-- MegaForm 01.06.28 — AI Knowledge: Templates + Rules + Feedback loop (2026-05-29)
--
-- Additive migration on top of 01.06.27 (MF_AI_Knowledge + History). Adds
-- 3 sibling tables to let the AI Form Assistant reach a tighter contract:
--
--   MF_AI_KB_Templates  — Many concrete templates (preset shapes / saved
--                         ops) per Knowledge entry. Pulls preset JSON out
--                         of the Examples column into a queryable form so
--                         each widget can carry an unbounded set of saved
--                         patterns (card-grid, table-list, cascade-2level
--                         ...) without bloating Body.
--
--   MF_AI_KB_Rules      — Hard-rejection rules indexed by RuleId (e.g.
--                         'DL-001'). chat.ts + ops.ts reference rules by
--                         RuleId instead of hand-coding the strings. When
--                         dispatcher rejects an op, it cites the RuleId
--                         and the AI can fetch the canonical FixHint.
--
--   MF_AI_KB_Feedback   — Every dispatcher rejection (or AI-self-reported
--                         failure) is logged here with the attempted op
--                         JSON + rejection message + the fix that worked.
--                         Admin reviews + promotes good rows into the
--                         Templates table → AI learns from the live loop.
--
-- All tables additive. No schema change on existing MF_AI_Knowledge or
-- MF_AI_Knowledge_History. Customer-edited rows survive every upgrade.

